<paragraph blockId="9.[151,840,1051,1111]" box="[151,434,1086,1111]" pageId="9">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,237,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1937,1959]" captionTargetBox="[300,1276,230,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[232,1364,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Distribution of Monohelea species in the Municipalities of Capitão Poço, Ourém, Tracuateua and Viseu from Northeast Mesoregion, and in the municipality of Santa Bárbara do Pará from Metropolitan Belém Mesoregion, Para State, Brazil." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067518/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
; 6 A–F; 10 A–B)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1158,2017]" pageId="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[158,280,1158,1183]" pageId="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The only Neotropical species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1917" box="[651,777,1158,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Monohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[651,777,1158,1182]" italics="true" pageId="9">Monohelea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which the males have brown legs with yellowish bands, hind femur with two mesal yellowish bands, paramere with two apical hook-shaped processes, one 
<date box="[1268,1302,1195,1219]" pageId="9">2X</date>
longer than other, aedeagus with base greatly expanded. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1158,2017]" pageId="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,273,1269,1294]" pageId="9">Male.</emphasis>
Head: eyes widely separated (
<figureCitation box="[619,715,1269,1294]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,355,1579]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,339,1596]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Monohelea gorayebi Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov., male. A. Wing; B. Thorax showing halter; C. Head, anterior view; D. Palpus, lateral view; E.Legs (left to right) of fore, mid-, hindlegs, lateral view; F. Genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067528/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Fig. 6 C</figureCitation>
). Antenna missing. Palpus (
<figureCitation box="[1031,1127,1269,1294]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,355,1579]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,339,1596]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Monohelea gorayebi Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov., male. A. Wing; B. Thorax showing halter; C. Head, anterior view; D. Palpus, lateral view; E.Legs (left to right) of fore, mid-, hindlegs, lateral view; F. Genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067528/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Fig. 6 D</figureCitation>
) brown; 3rd segment nearly oval, with large, deep, sensory organ on distal 1/2; lengths of segments 15- 28- 30- 25- 50; palpal ratio 1.5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1158,2017]" pageId="9">
Thorax. Brown, with pattern of yellowish patches, not defined on slide mounted specimen. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[1331,1428,1341,1366]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,355,1579]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,339,1596]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Monohelea gorayebi Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov., male. A. Wing; B. Thorax showing halter; C. Head, anterior view; D. Palpus, lateral view; E.Legs (left to right) of fore, mid-, hindlegs, lateral view; F. Genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067528/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Fig. 6 E</figureCitation>
) brown; coxae and trochanters brown; femora with two mesal yellowish bands; tibiofemora joints yellowish; tibiae with subbasal and mesal yellowish bands; hind tibial comb with 6 bristles. Tarsi: pale; fore tarsus missing; hind tarsomere 1 with one basal and one apical spine; midtarsomere 1 with 2 basal, 2 apical spines; apical spines of mid-, hind tarsomeres 2–4: 2-2-1, 1-1-1, basal spines absent; mid-, hind tarsal ratios 2.23, 1.82; claws missing. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[159,257,1524,1549]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,355,1579]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,339,1596]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Monohelea gorayebi Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov., male. A. Wing; B. Thorax showing halter; C. Head, anterior view; D. Palpus, lateral view; E.Legs (left to right) of fore, mid-, hindlegs, lateral view; F. Genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067528/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Fig. 6 A</figureCitation>
): macrotrichia restricted to vein costa; microtrichia absent; 2nd radial cell nearly 
<date box="[1157,1191,1525,1549]" pageId="9">2X</date>
longer than 1st; wing length 
<quantity box="[228,330,1560,1584]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.02" pageId="9" unit="mm" value="1.02">1.02 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[412,515,1560,1584]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="9" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
; costal ratio 0.75. Halter stem pale; knob brown in distal 1/2 (
<figureCitation box="[1208,1302,1560,1585]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,355,1579]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,339,1596]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Monohelea gorayebi Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov., male. A. Wing; B. Thorax showing halter; C. Head, anterior view; D. Palpus, lateral view; E.Legs (left to right) of fore, mid-, hindlegs, lateral view; F. Genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067528/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Fig. 6 B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1158,2017]" pageId="9">
Abdomen. Brown. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[546,658,1596,1621]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[166,1419,355,1579]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,339,1596]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Monohelea gorayebi Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov., male. A. Wing; B. Thorax showing halter; C. Head, anterior view; D. Palpus, lateral view; E.Legs (left to right) of fore, mid-, hindlegs, lateral view; F. Genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067528/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Figs. 6 F</figureCitation>
; 10 A–B): sternite IX spiculate except on basal portion, posterior margin not defined; tergite IX tapering with a pair of apicolateral processes, each with 4 setae. Gonocoxite moderately stout, nearly 
<date box="[436,470,1669,1693]" pageId="9">2X</date>
longer than basal width, with a submesal internal sclerotized projection; gonostylus nearly straight 0.88X as long as gonocoxite, moderately pilose on basal 3/4. Parameres swollen (
<figureCitation box="[1228,1336,1704,1729]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[181,1418,207,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[165,1429,193,1937]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Parameres and aedeagus. A–B. Monohelea gorayebi Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov.; C–D. Monohelea patauateua Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp.nov.; E–F.Monohelea visinensis Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067536/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Fig. 10 A</figureCitation>
) 2.2X as long as aedeagus, largely fused dorsally at base; apical portion with two strong hook-shaped processes laterally directed, one 
<date box="[307,342,1776,1800]" pageId="9">2X</date>
longer than other. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[690,801,1776,1801]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[181,1418,207,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[165,1429,193,1937]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Parameres and aedeagus. A–B. Monohelea gorayebi Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov.; C–D. Monohelea patauateua Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp.nov.; E–F.Monohelea visinensis Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067536/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Fig. 10 B</figureCitation>
) triangular, composed of 2 pointed ventral plates, each with a delicately sclerotized apical projection, which arises in the aedeagus base; basal arms large, greatly expanded laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1158,2017]" box="[199,418,1884,1909]" pageId="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1884,1909]" pageId="9">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
